{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"baking tray, frying pan, grill, hob","id":"r281586","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-CSNKm9ciqrk\/XZQH4xCmjpI\/AAAAAAAAcNM\/hcSPyuoRaHEncAk0QoqDWsXwEo03wW3iQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_t4zOeRzZN42mMIh5.png","title":"Chicken Tikka Flatbreads","publishedAt":"2018-12-03T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ingredients"},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Tikka Sauce"},{"content":"3 garlic cloves"},{"content":"10 g fresh root ginger, peeled, cut in round slices (2 mm)"},{"content":"80 g onions, quartered"},{"content":"20 g olive oil, plus 1 Tbsp for frying"},{"content":"2 tsp ground cumin"},{"content":"2 tsp ground coriander"},{"content":"2 tsp paprika"},{"content":"2 tsp garam masala"},{"content":"1 tsp ground turmeric"},{"content":"1 ½ tsp chilli powder"},{"content":"½ tsp caster sugar"},{"content":"½ tsp ground cinnamon"},{"content":"½ tsp fine sea salt"},{"content":"400 g tinned chopped tomatoes"},{"content":"100 g double cream"},{"content":"500 g chicken thighs, skinless, boneless, diced (2 cm)"},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Assembly"},{"content":"4 naan breads (see tip)"},{"content":"1 red onion, sliced (5 mm)"},{"content":"100 g natural yoghurt"},{"content":"fresh coriander leaves, for garnishing"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"41 g","fat":"40.2 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"81 g","calories":"3644 kJ \/ 870 kcal"},"preparations":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Preparation"},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Tikka Sauce"},{"content":"Place garlic, ginger, onions and 20 g oil in mixing bowl then chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add cumin, coriander, paprika, garam masala, turmeric, chilli powder, sugar, cinnamon and salt then sauté <b>2 min\/120°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add tomatoes and cream then, with simmering basket in place of measuring cup, cook <b>15 min\/110°C\/speed 2<b>. Meanwhile, heat 1 Tbsp oil in a frying pan over a medium-high heat. Add chicken and fry for 4-6 minutes or until cooked and golden on all sides."},{"content":"Blend sauce <strong><b>20 sec\/speed 5<b>-9, increasing speed gradually<\/strong>. Add pan-fried chicken then stir with spatula to combine."},{"content":"Preheat grill to medium heat."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Assembly"},{"content":"Divide chicken tikka mixture between naan breads."},{"content":"Transfer 2 naan breads to a baking tray then grill for 2-3 minutes until brown around the edges. Repeat with remaining 2 naan breads."},{"content":"Top each naan bread with sliced onion, 1-2 Tbsp yoghurt and fresh coriander then serve warm."}],"hintsAndTricks":["This recipe uses shop-bought naan bread for a quicker meal, but if time allows, make your own naan in your Thermomix. See <i>A Taste of India<\/i> for recipes.","This fun dinner is a cross between a chicken tikka masala and a pizza! Chicken thigh pieces are stirred through a flavourful tikka sauce, then spooned onto fluffy naan breads before being placed under the grill for a few minutes to brown. Topped with fresh coriander and tangy yoghurt, these flatbreads are a delicious, family-friendly alternative to a traditional curry."],"basicInfo":["easy","35m","45m","4 portions"]}